Guerrillas hit Turkish emplacements in southern Kurdistan

HPG guerrillas hit the Turkish invasion forces on Hill Lelikan, leaving one soldier dead.

 ANF

 BEHDINAN

 Sunday, 22 Apr 2018, 15:00

The Press and Communications Center of People’s Defense Forces (HPG-BIM) reported that guerrillas targeted Turkish military units stationed on Hill Lelikan within the boundaries of southern Kurdistan.

According to the statement by HPG-BIM, Turkish forces’ emplacements came under intense fire from two directions at 18:30 on April 21. One soldier was killed as a result of the action.

